article.headline: Robert Morris 70, Fairleigh Dickinson 66
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- A.J. Jackson scored a game-high 21 points -- including two key baskets in the final two minutes -- as Robert Morris rallied for a 70-66 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night. FDU (8-7, 3-1 in Northeast Conference) was clinging to a 64-63 lead when Jackson hit a turnaround jumper with 1:58 left. The Knights, though, regained the lead when Andre Harris hit two free throws with 42.7 seconds remaining. Jackson then put the Colonials (11-4, 3-3) ahead for good when he made a layup with 16.8 seconds left and drew a foul on the play. He then made the free throw to complete the 3-point play and give his team a 68-66 lead. FDU then had a chance to tie, but Mezie Nwigwe stole the ball from Cameron Tyler and was fouled by Michael Peeples with 3.2 seconds left. Nwigwe then sealed the win by hitting both free throws, and the Knights could not get another shot off. Derek Coleman added 18 points for Robert Morris, while Nwigwe finished with 12 points and Jeremy Chappell had 10 points and 10 rebounds. Harris led the Knights with 20 points and 11 rebounds, while Manny Ubilla had 14 points and 10 rebounds, eight assists and three steals.
